Reviews: ["This TV arrived in 4 days via UPS in excellent condition. No damage to the outside carton or to the TV.Physical unpacking and set up was easy. Complying with all the Samsung setup conditions was intrusive and offensive. It left a bad taste. It could use an additional HDMI port and traditional RCA jacks (red, yellow, white). It would be charitable to describe the remote as minimalist. We purchased an inexpensive universal remote with real channel buttons and functional controls and it made a positive difference. Voice control isn't a necessary feature for us. This TV meets our requirements but it's a bit pricey for what you get.", "the remote is to small and not enough control buttons . I don't like the fact I have to go through screens to get to controls .the lack of inputs on side is a design problem. you cant change the picture ratio. volume control needs to be better. picture and sound is nice ,voice control remote is a mixed bag, The internet part is quite is good .I really like Samsung but this tv is a rather Big disappointment. The size of the mounting bolts size is WRONG BIG TIME IN GOOGLE.ITS A DECENT TV BUT IT Should have been design a lot better.", 'Great display, sound, and performance. Title: TCL 43" 4-SERIES 4K UHD HDR ROKU SMART TV 43S425 Television
Reviews: ['So, assuming you’re already a TCL Roku tv owner, this has all the greatness of the previous models. It still has the electrical burning smell, which a lot of the types of TVs have. Not just this brand. There is just the one thing. When you hit the power button and turn it off, the screen does not fully turn off. There is a very low backlight that is always on. I read about this not being “an issue” but rather a complete annoyance. All I can really say is deal with it, buy a WiFi outlet (like I did) and turn it off/unplug it after use or simply buy a new one. The QLEDs are supposed to be a much larger jump in greatness. Overall I’m happy with it but I hope the board doesn’t overheat and burn out the board due to this light being on. And it is not the indicator LED. If you go to the Roku forums, there is a lengthy discussion about this issue. But it’s still a great value and pictures. I’ll probably never go to another brand. Just keep upgrading after a couple years. ', 'I’ve already purchased this TV a couple years back and had it for 2 years without any issues or picture quality loss. I sold the tv and that’s why I had bought a new one recently. But without a doubt great value! ', "Make sure you protect your TV, bought 2 and broke one on my own error of trying to just balance it. Good product, works well though my crappy phone doesn't screen mirror as it says it could.. but good size and beautiful display and tons of Roku Channels. Lots of free content. ", 'Bought for a gift and my daughter and her kids love it. Alll they have to decide is who has control of the remote.', 'Very good picture quality easy set easy to use Easy on the wallet.', 'This tv has a great picture and good sound quality especially for an awesome price. You will not be disappointed if you make this purchase ', 'Easy to setup. Crisp picture. Fairly lightweight. Works well with Chromecast. ', 'I love it good picture', 'remote must be close to tv to work even with new batteries', 'Why get an overpriced TV, when this TV has amazing image quality and a built in Roku!  I’m a gigantic fan!!!  It’s like having an Apple TV built into the TV!!!!  A+++++++']

Reviews: ['The images on the screen are even more clear than what we had with our previous tv. Title: Samsung The Frame QN32LS03T 32" 1080p QLED Smart TV - Charcoal Black
Reviews: ["Overall great tv art frame, a little overpriced for what you get. Had real issues with internet connection since once you were turn it off completely it was asking for password and sometime even you where entering the password it wasn't taking it, had to call Samsung several times until last time the remote it and made some changes on the settings and fix it. I hate the once Box to make the connection since its hard to hide it, it doesn't make sense at all. Picture is good, volume is ok compare to the size 32 not really impressed. This version doesn't have the motion sensor to turn the frame once you near it, I think it starts from 43 inch and up, I am not sure how much the sensor would cost to Samsung to add it since all 32 and up all have it unless they considering this base model. Main reason to buy this was a frame 5 stars to it, as TV i would rate it 2-3 stars since you can buy larger size with better pictures and audio quality. Dont pay more than $500 for this one since is not worth it, or go larger size since it has more features. ", "I needed a tv to watch the news in the morning when my family is having breakfast but won't use it all the time.  It has a feature where you can upload your own art photos and it will display them in a slide show.  The resolution being 4k,  makes the paintings look almost real and with a custom frame around the television, you don't even notice that it is a tv.  Since it was an open box item, I got it at a discount and it was in perfect working condition.", "This is an ok tv as far as picture is concern.  I got this because of the frame, the low profile design and it works well for my bedroom.  I like to look at photos.  The quality of the photos are good.  There is light reflection that I can't do anything about it even though I blinded my windows and shut off the lights inside my room. Other than that, the photos look sharp.  You need to sign up with Samsung to get access to their art gallery.  ", "I really like this, I think even at the lower than anywhere else price...it's not worth stretching to buy THIS EXACT model...but I thought it would be a really nice extra for the gym room on a house I am renovating I may later turn into a vacation rental. It was a lot easier to set up than my new printer! The colors are vivid and it is very professional looking, it's what I would place in a professional office.", 'No motion sensor.  Will turn off at night (no light) but does not turn back on next morning (with light). SmartThings app  unreliable which causes art mode to freeze and makes accessing art mode difficult. Samsung customer service is useless. Just purchase a tv with usb for less.', 'If you want a wall mounted 32inch tv with essentially no profile, look no further.', 'Showed up looking perfectly fine but would not power up, requests for exchange were ignored ']

Reviews: ["TV is easy to set up and unbox. Only issue I had is HDMI inputs are slightly off and are difficult to plug in. I have seen others have had this issue. Title: Samsung UN50AU8000 50 Inch UHD 4K Crystal UHD Smart LED TV (2021)
Reviews: ["This TV arrived in 4 days via UPS in excellent condition. No damage to the outside carton or to the TV.Physical unpacking and set up was easy. Complying with all the Samsung setup conditions was intrusive and offensive. It left a bad taste. It could use an additional HDMI port and traditional RCA jacks (red, yellow, white). It would be charitable to describe the remote as minimalist. We purchased an inexpensive universal remote with real channel buttons and functional controls and it made a positive difference. Voice control isn't a necessary feature for us. This TV meets our requirements but it's a bit pricey for what you get.", "the remote is to small and not enough control buttons . I don't like the fact I have to go through screens to get to controls .the lack of inputs on side is a design problem. you cant change the picture ratio. volume control needs to be better. picture and sound is nice ,voice control remote is a mixed bag, The internet part is quite is good .I really like Samsung but this tv is a rather Big disappointment. The size of the mounting bolts size is WRONG BIG TIME IN GOOGLE.ITS A DECENT TV BUT IT Should have been design a lot better.", 'Great display, sound, and performance. A great investment if you want an excellent TV for the$$$$. Definitely recommend it to anyone with a low budget or that don’t want to spend too much on a TV.', 'Beautiful, bright picture. Minimalist remote (but replete with features).', 'Good quality picture. Smart features are great.  Speakers are OK.', "Great Tv good picture. okay there's just so much you say about a tv.", 'great picture,.a little hard to navigate,and remote code not displayed clearly if at all.', 'This is an excellent TV, right out of the box very easy to set up, if you have another Samsung TV you can transfer your settings from that TV to this new TV. Very easy setup this way. Picture is crystal clear!', 'Relatively easy to set up and has a great picture.  ', "The picture is clear as a bell and it was easy to hang on the wall. I bought an articulating mount so we could watch from any angle. I still haven't tried all the goodies available and maybe I'm too dumb for a smart TV. Anyway, we love it."]
